# ================ Additions : Entities

# Code Button
A button active to players or holdables, can be used to setup a code sequence for the map, each code of the button can be identical or overlapped

# Code Button Target Controller
Sets up the correct password for the certain code button group

# Flag Listener Stopclock Controller
A controller that starts a stopclock counting when a flag is enabled

# Flag Packer (SSC)
Pack up a series of flags into a "bag"

# Fnt Display series
Sort of like Custom Core Message, but instead of using the map default font, you can choose your font from the fnt file!

# Set Flag Controller
Mostly for my personal usages, but feel free to try it, it sets up a series of flags under a certain occassion, supports inverted flags and global flags

# Settings Override Controller
Ever thinking about forcing the fullscreen or rescale the screen for some reason? Well, here it is

# Camera Grid (Loenn entity)
A decorative entity that show a grid of camera offset

# BG Tiles Collide Controller
A controller detecting whether the player is colliding with the BG Tiles

# Comprehensive Controller
A controller that records data and transform them into session data of the level, inspired from Kosei Helper GameData Controller

# Condition Delay Listener
When a certain condition is met, either flag sequences or ChroniaHelper Math Expressions, or FrostHelper Session Expressions, the flags will be set after a certain delay

# HUD Controller
ChroniaHelper contains a loads of HUDs now, which can be seen in the options, but what if the mapper wants some of the HUD area to be clear and the player still wanna keep their HUD active?
Well use this controller to temporarily hide some of them

# ================ Additions : Triggers

# Clear Packed Flags Trigger

# Password Keyboard Trigger (SSC)
The trigger version of Password Keyboard

# Random Packed Flag Trigger (SSC)
When entering the trigger, the level will pick out a random flag out of the packed flags by Packed Flags Controller, when this flag is picked out and set, the flag will not be picked out again until all other flags in the bag are all picked out, then the bag will reset
So, imagine that you put a bunch of sticks in a pot, you pick out a stick and throw it away, but if you throw them all away, then you start picking them up and put them back into the pot

# ================ Additions : Features

# Modified Animated Parallax
An alternative version of Maddie's animated parallax, giving you the full control on whether the animation should be playing or not, or how fast it should play etc.
Check the bgs/ChroniaHelper/modifiedParallax in the helper for usage examples

# ================ Optimizations

Now most message displayer that allows mapper to fill in a Dialog ID now supports session keys, which can be set up by some other entities, to access session keys, use "#" before the Dialog ID to indicate it
